# Ticket Writing Conventions

## Title Format
`[Tool Type] [Project Name] - Ask summary`

### Tool Type Prefixes
| Prefix | When to use |
|--------|-------------|
| RLS | Row-level security related tickets |
| HEX | HEX dashboard or reporting related |
| Airtable | Airtable automation or data related |
| AT Tooling | General automation tooling |
| Miscellaneous | When no specific tool type applies |

### Examples
- "RLS - [Project Alpha] Add role-based filtering to dashboard"
- "HEX - [Analytics] Fix broken chart visualization"
- "Airtable - [Project Odysseus] Automate weekly report sync"
- "AT Tooling - [Project Odysseus] Modify Autoreviewer to check spelling"
- "Miscellaneous - Investigate slow API response times"

### When Tool Type or Project is Unknown
If you cannot infer the tool type or project name from context:
- Skip the placeholder entirely
- Use a clear, descriptive summary instead
- Example: "Fix login timeout issue for mobile users"

## Description Template

```markdown
## Summary
1-2 sentences. What is needed and why it matters.

## Ask Spec 
The ideal ask/end state as described by the reporter. If not provided
or ambiguous, note "Needs scoping."

## What is Being Blocked?
What step or process is stopped/hindered to complete the ask. If nothing is blocked, note "No immediate blockers."

## Timeline 
When this needs to be done and why. If nothing is mentioned, note "No specific deadline mentioned."

## Slack Context
[Link to original Slack thread](permalink)
Reporter: @username
Channel: #channel-name
```

## Priority Guide

| Priority | Level | When to use | Response SLA |
|----------|-------|-------------|--------------|
| Urgent (P0) | 1 | Experience-breaking; customer asked ASAP; can't do tasks right now | < 4 hours |
| High (P1) | 2 | Blocking project start or key improvement; tight 24hr SLA | < 24 hours |
| Medium (P2) | 3 | Important but not critical; ~3 days acceptable | < 3 days |
| Low (P3) | 4 | Wishlist items; nice-to-have improvements | Best effort |

Default SLA is 24 hours. For <24hr SLA, the ticket must explain why
and the reporter should DM Arunavha Chanda, Dylan Pourkay, or oncall
AND Jordan Winawer.

### Priority Keywords Reference
| Keywords in request | Suggested priority |
|---------------------|-------------------|
| "urgent", "P0", "blocking", "down", "production", "broken flow", "can't do tasks" | Urgent (1) |
| "blocking project", "tight deadline", "need ASAP", "P1" | High (2) |
| "nice-to-have", "important but not critical", "P2", "when possible" | Medium (3) |
| "wishlist", "when you get a chance", "low pri", "P3", "eventually" | Low (4) |

## Type Classification

| Type | Keywords | When to use |
|------|----------|-------------|
| Bug | "timeout", "crash", "error", "broken", "bug", "regression", "failing", "not working" | Something that worked before is now broken |
| Feature | "add", "support", "enable", "allow", "new", "feature", "request", "want", "need" | New functionality that doesn't exist |
| Improvement | "improve", "optimize", "refactor", "clean up", "better", "faster", "enhance" | Making existing functionality better |
| Task | "update", "change", "migrate", "move", "rename", "configure", "setup" | General work that isn't a bug/feature/improvement |

**Default if unclear:** Task

## Key Principles

1. **Filing the ticket is the priority.** A ticket with full thread context but missing some fields is better than no ticket. Always capture the full conversation.

2. **Context over perfection.** Include as much relevant information as possible, even if formatting isn't perfect.

3. **Be explicit about unknowns.** If something is unclear, say so rather than guessing. Use "Needs scoping" or "Unknown" as appropriate.

4. **Link back to Slack.** Always include the Slack permalink so anyone can find the original discussion.

## Optional Slack↔Linear Linking
If the user explicitly asks BearBot to link conversation + ticket:
- Use Slack↔Linear sync/linking (thread connected to Linear issue)
- Post Linear ticket URL in the same Slack thread
- Treat this as optional; do not do it by default

## Default Status
- If ticket is assigned to an engineer at creation time, default state should be `Todo`
- If ticket is unassigned, keep default triage/backlog behavior

## Labels (Optional)
If the request clearly fits one of these categories, add the appropriate label:
- `needs-scoping` — Requirements are unclear
- `blocked` — Waiting on external dependency
- `quick-win` — Can be completed in < 1 hour
- `customer-facing` — Affects external users
